ica is a certified public accountant and a member of the American Institute of CPAs. She is married to Larry, with whom she shares a recently empty nest. She has a diversity of interests and hobbies outside of work, her family and dogs being chief among them.Fun FactShe proved that hard work pays off. Even after seven years away from corporate America, she scored highest out of nearly 5,000 candidates in the State of Maryland CPA exam in 1999. Never doubt the tenacity and smarts of a “stay at home” mom.PrincipalNina MitchellNina MitchellPrincipalAboutNina has over 25 years of finance, tax and investment advisory experience, primarily with an elite group of professional athletes, executives and high net worth individuals. As a Bridgewater Principal, she co-leads the firm’s overall management, marketing and corporate policy. As senior member of the firm’s Investment Committee, she co-directs the company’s investment policies, recommendations and asset allocation strategies, in addition to providing personal financial planning and investment advisory services for clients. Prior to joining Bridgewater, Nina was a Principal and co-Founder of MTX Wealth Management, LLC for eight years, and served as President of SFX Financial Advisory Management Enterprises, Inc. for five years prior. She has held other past senior executive positions at sports management companies, focusing her expertise in providing financial and investment advice to professional athletes.Nina earned a bachelor’s degree in Accounting from the University of Maryland. She holds the Series 65 license, and is currently a non-practicing Certified Public Accountant. She is a board member of the Boomer Esiason Foundation, Arthur Ashe Learning Center and the Lymphatic Malformation Institute. She loves biking, walking, traveling and spending time with family and friends, especially her husband, Jason, and their two children.Fun FactShe has been featured in several journalistic articles, including an April 1998 appearance in the Sunday Business Section of The New York Times.Managing PrincipalRon RubinPrincipal and Chief Investment OfficerSteve SchulerSteve SchulerPrincipal and Chief Investment OfficerAboutSteve has more than 25 years helping families build investment portfolios.  Before joining Bridgewater, he was President, Partner and head of the Investment Committee at Maryland Capital Management for 14 years. Steve manages the Quality Growth Stock (QGS) strategy, develops portfolio management and asset allocation tactics, leads research efforts, provides overall investment models, and is responsible for making manager and fund recommendations. He also advises and is the portfolio manager for select clients.Steve earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science from Hobart College in Geneva, New York. He is also a graduate of the Securities Industry Institute at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania. From 1988 to 1999, Steve was a Director and Principal at Deutsche Bank Alex. Brown.Steve is a member of the board of trustees of the St. Paul’s School for Boys, where he serves on its investment and philanthropy committees. He volunteers at Habitat for Humanity of the Chesapeake. He is a skier and squash player during the winter, and a tennis player and cyclist in the warmer seasons. He is married to Megan, with whom he has three children, Seth, Brad and Claire.Fun FactSteve has a keen interest supporting efforts to preserve and restore the environmental integrity of our natural habitat and resources. He recently joined the board of the National Park Trust, a Rockville, MD based non-profit that provides programs to preserve and better utilize our nation’s National and State Parks.Senior Investment Advisor and Director of Financial PlanningShellie Kurek PetersShellie Kurek PetersSenior Investment Advisor and Director of Financial PlanningAboutShellie’s experience includes over 20 years of advising individuals, families and business owners.  Her wealth management and financial planning expertise provides valued insights and recommendations in such areas as: cash flow analysis, risk management, estate and trust planning, investment management, and charitable planning strategies.  She serves a core group of the firm’s clients, overseeing all aspects of the relationship. Working alongside the firm’s leadership, Shellie develops and delivers holistic integrated wealth management strategies.This customized high-touch support helps our clients to define and articulate their goals while allowing us to create structures to improve desired outcomes. Shellie earned her Bachelor of Arts degree from St. John Fisher College in Rochester, New York. In addition to consulting and advisory roles, she has held a variety of management positions, including tenure at Wilmington Trust, N.A. and Deloitte Investment Advisors. She holds the Series 65 license and is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner. Shellie has also served as a member, treasurer and/or director of a number of volunteer organizations. Married with two children, Shellie enjoys spending time with her family, reading, traveling and more traveling.Fun FactShe founded The Boston Philanthropic Advisors Roundtable, a multidisciplinary organization to share ideas, educate and connect like-minded professionals in the Boston area.Senior Investment AssociateJessica JarosikJessica JarosikSenior Investment AssociateAboutJessica works with the Director of Financial Planning on client financial plans. Jessica serves as an investment advisor to a select group of clients. She is also the point of contact for a select group of clients, monitoring portfolio performance, producing quarterly reports and preparing portfolio review materials. She began her career as a Grants Management Specialist at the National Institutes of Health. She later worked as an Economist at the Bureau of Economic Analysis. Jessica holds a BA in economics, government and politics from University of Maryland. S