ting with a specialty in financial accounting. He worked in finance for Marriott Hotels and Troika Entertainment before coming to Bridgewater. Ryan is interested in the relationship between finance and technology, and is always trying to find new and more efficient ways to incorporate the two. He has a BA in accounting from Towson University.Fun FactRyan went to high school at the American School of Warsaw Poland, where he played three sports (basketball, volleyball, and baseball) and got to see most of Eastern Europe by the time he was 18.Principal and Chief Investment OfficerSteve SchulerSteve SchulerPrincipal and Chief Investment OfficerAboutSteve has more than 25 years helping families build investment portfolios.  Before joining Bridgewater, he was President, Partner and head of the Investment Committee at Maryland Capital Management for 14 years. Steve manages the Quality Growth Stock (QGS) strategy, develops portfolio management and asset allocation tactics, leads research efforts, provides overall investment models, and is responsible for making manager and fund recommendations. He also advises and is the portfolio manager for select clients.Steve earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science from Hobart College in Geneva, New York. He is also a graduate of the Securities Industry Institute at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania. From 1988 to 1999, Steve was a Director and Principal at Deutsche Bank Alex. Brown.Steve is a member of the board of trustees of the St. Paul’s School for Boys, where he serves on its investment and philanthropy committees. He volunteers at Habitat for Humanity of the Chesapeake. He is a skier and squash player during the winter, and a tennis player and cyclist in the warmer seasons. He is married to Megan, with whom he has three children, Seth, Brad and Claire.Fun FactSteve has a keen interest supporting efforts to preserve and restore the environmental integrity of our natural habitat and resources. He recently joined the board of the National Park Trust, a Rockville, MD based non-profit that provides programs to preserve and better utilize our nation’s National and State Parks.Director of Financial Management and Family Office ServicesPaul ShaperoPaul ShaperoDirector of Financial Management and Family Office ServicesAboutPaul provides financial management services to individuals and families. Acting as a personal accountant, Paul manages clients’ day-to-day financial responsibilities, including bills, mortgages, budgeting, and monthly spending and cash flow reporting. He combines his accounting skills with a natural ability to anticipate future possibilities to create positive client outcomes.He loves the diversity of his work, and prides himself in providing excellent client service. Paul holds a BS in accounting from University College at the University of Maryland.  A fitness enthusiast, when he’s not crunching numbers, he’s likely crunching his abs.Fun FactOne of his favorite quotes is, “No matter how rocky the seas, the ship must come in.” Sounds like something Paul might say, don’t you think?Director of Business DevelopmentBill TinklepaughBill TinklepaughDirector of Business DevelopmentAboutBill leads and manages Bridgewater’s client expansion by identifying growth opportunities, and introducing new clients to the benefits of professional investment advising and financial management. Bill brings a reputation for honesty, integrity and excellence to his role, as well as nearly 40 years of experience developing key business relationships as an economist, U.S. diplomat, federal lobbyist, industry spokesperson and senior government relations executive.Bill began his career as an agricultural economist with the Trade Negotiations Division of the Foreign Agricultural Service in the U.S. Department of Agriculture. After holding positions of increasing responsibility over an 11-year period, including two overseas assignments, Bill began serving as Vice President and Director of Economics for the International Dairy Foods Association, representing the $70 billion dairy processing industry in Washington, D.C. In subsequent leadership positions with Master Dairies, Inc., and most recently, Dean Foods Company, he has played a pivotal role in shaping the dairy industry—one of the nation’s most competitive.  He holds a B.S. in agricultural business and marketing from Rutgers University, and an M.S. in agricultural economics from the University of Maryland. Bill holds the Series 65 license.Fun FactHe was one of the people behind the nationally acclaimed “milk mustache” advertising campaign, organizing industry support for it as the first industry-wide $110 million promotional program for fluid milk.Investment AnalystJake WeinrebJake WeinrebInvestment AnalystAboutJake researches financial markets and runs analyses for client holdings. He performs in-depth research on the proprietary Quality Growth Stock portfolio including preparing company reports on stocks, developing and updating watch lists, and participating in conference calls. He conducts analysis and due-diligence on mutual funds and private investment funds. Jake holds a B.S. in Mathematics and Economics from American University. Pre-Bridgewater, Jake interned at the Department of Homeland Security, Office of the Chief Financial Advisor; and Hall Capital Partners.Jake's greatest interest is in the analysis and synthesis of macro financial data into actionable investment theses.In June 2014, Jake completed the CFA Level 1 exam and he plans to become a Chartered Financial Analyst in the near future.Fun FactJake is most relaxed at the beach and his first job was as a lifeguard at a swimming pool.Senior Financial AssociateTony WilliamsTony WilliamsSenior Financial AssociateAboutWith more more than 18 years of financial planning, budgeting and investment portfolio management experience, Tony works with professional athletes and high net worth individuals. He is responsible for financial planning, meeting preparation, cash management, monetary transfers and client services. Tony is an important member of our Financial management team where he helps with investment implementations, financial budgeting, estate planning and portfolio tracking in service to our clients.Tony earned a bachelor’s degree in Finance from the University of Maryland. His first industry position was inputting trades at the investment firm Legg Mason. Directly prior to joining Bridgewater, he was Operations Manager at MTX Wealth Management.Tony holds a Series 65 license. He volunteers for the Special Olympics, and is an avid camper and golfer. He enjoys relaxing in nature with his wife and son.Fun FactHe served 22 years in the U.S. Navy, where he was responsible for training military assault units deploying overseas.The Pulse of BridgewaterWe like to think that our high employee retention rates have something to do with the care we put into the culture at Bridgewater. Since we’re ambitious, getting along and working well together is just the beginning. We’re dedicated to personal growth and physical health, and share an ongoing commitment to creating high quality relationships in all areas of our lives.Conscious leadership is at the heart of Bridgewater culture. We offer in-house programs including weekly leadership conversations, quarterly conscious leadership retreats, and ongoing support so that we develop leadership skills that will benefit us, Bridgewater and our clients. We provide access to yoga classes offsite and offer meditation and other wellness activities on site.We genuinely like spending time together, both in and outside of work. We’re all dedicated to our families, and we also make time to have fun and relax with our Bridgewater family. We know this sounds too good to be true, but it is. And we’re willing to do the work it takes to keep our culture operating at such a high level. We’re in finance after all; we spend a lot of time at work. It better be fantastic!Remember the good times.Here are some shots from our latest events. Please join us for our next one. We love to see you out and about. Then we can put fun pictures of you here.Washington Capitals GameEvening with Nils Lofgren ServicesINDIVIDUALS & FAMILIESInvestment AdvisoryFinancial PlanningTax AdvisoryFamily OfficeINSTITUTIONS & BUSINESSESInvestment AdvisoryTax AdvisoryOutsourced CFOAboutAboutOur TeamGallery & EventsBlogHer WealthMiscPrivacy PolicyConnectContactLinkedin© 2015 Copyright, Bridgewater Wealth Management. All rights reserved.






