Bridgewater Wealth Joins Focus Financial


January 19, 2010, 07:36:16 PM EDT
By FA Magazine Staff, Financial Advisor Magazine









































Shutterstock photo


Focus Financial Partners LLC on Tuesday announced it added
Bridgewater Wealth & Financial Management LLC to its roster of
partner firms. Terms of the deal weren't disclosed. 
Focus Financial Partners LLC on Tuesday announced it added
Bridgewater Wealth & Financial Management LLC to its roster of
partner firms. Terms of the deal weren't disclosed.
Based in Bethesda, Md., Bridgewater Wealth is a combination RIA
and CPA practice founded by Ron Rubin and Gary Kasnett. The firm
has offices in Washington, D.C. and New York City, and manages $200
million in assets. 
Focus Financial has bought stakes in 19 wealth management firms
with more than $33 billion in assets since it was launched in 2006.
Based in New York, Focus typically purchases equity stakes of 40%
to 70% in its partner firms. In return, it promises to provide
advisory practices with the technology, back office support and
scale needed to grow their business while retaining their
independence.
The acquisition strategy is aimed at achieving the critical mass
needed to take the entity public.



The views and opinions expressed herein are the views and opinions of the author and do not necessarily reflect those of Nasdaq, Inc.



Copyright © 2010 Charter Financial Publishing Network Inc. All Rights Reserved.







